# Testing Conventions

## Context

Excalidraw uses Vitest + jsdom. Many browser APIs (canvas, fonts, RAF, matchMedia, IndexedDB) are mocked globally in `setupTests.ts`. Tests range from pure unit tests to full UI interaction tests that render the React component and simulate pointer/keyboard input.

## Rule

### Test helpers тАФ use what exists

- **Element creation:** use `API.createElement({ type, x, y, ... })` from `packages/excalidraw/tests/helpers/api.ts` тАФ never construct raw element objects manually
- **UI interaction:** use `UI`, `Keyboard`, and `mouse` / `Pointer` helpers from `packages/excalidraw/tests/helpers/ui.ts` instead of firing raw DOM events
- **Component rendering:** use `renderApp(<Excalidraw />)` from `packages/excalidraw/tests/test-utils.ts`, not bare `render()` тАФ it waits for canvas initialization and resets pointer state
- **Scene mutation in tests:** use `API.setElements()` and `API.updateElement()`, not direct `scene.*` calls
- **Actions:** use `API.executeAction(action)` to trigger action manager actions

### Snapshots

- Always pass partial matchers for non-deterministic fields: `expect(el).toMatchSnapshot({ id: expect.any(String), seed: expect.any(Number), versionNonce: expect.any(Number) })`
- NEVER update snapshots without reviewing the diff тАФ snapshot regressions in `packages/common/src/__snapshots__/colors.test.ts.snap` indicate palette changes that affect every user

### Mocking

- `throttleRAF` is already mocked globally (executes immediately) тАФ do not mock it again per-test
- Canvas operations are handled by `vitest-canvas-mock` globally тАФ do not stub `getContext`
- Use `vi.spyOn` + `vi.restoreAllMocks()` in `afterEach` when spying on globals
- Use helpers from `packages/excalidraw/tests/helpers/mocks.ts` for `HTMLImageElement` mocking (`mockHTMLImageElement`, `mockMultipleHTMLImageElements`)
- NEVER use `vi.mock()` at module level for `@excalidraw/*` packages тАФ path aliases resolve to source

### Coverage

- Branch coverage threshold is 70% тАФ the highest of all thresholds; ensure conditional paths are tested
- Run `yarn test:app` (not individual file runs) to validate coverage thresholds are met

### Test location

- Colocate tests with source: `foo.ts` тЖТ `foo.test.ts` in the same directory
- Exception: `packages/excalidraw/tests/` for integration-level tests that render the full `<Excalidraw />` component
- Custom spatial assertions: use `expect(...).toCloselyEqualPoints(points, precision)` from `packages/utils/src/test-utils.ts` for floating-point coordinate comparisons

## How to verify

1. Run `yarn test:app` тАФ all tests must pass
2. Run `yarn test:app --coverage` тАФ confirm branch coverage stays тЙе 70%
3. For snapshot changes, run `yarn test:app -u` and review every changed snapshot deliberately
